On 2001-07-19 01:05, Snakey Snarefoot wrote:
Hi there!

Of course it's not for high levels only :)

Ok down to some answers here:
I usually spend level 11 to 13 doing dervs in North Ro. There are 3 derv camps there but you should only attempt 2 of them. Derv camp 1 has a named Dark Elf in it (Dorn). Don't go there :)
Derv 2 is the biggest camp, 6 dervs spawn there. You have to have a good group - OR - you can play MR. COOLGUY and singlepull them with harmony. They should start indifferently to you and it will take many dervs to get them KOS to you. So you can safely walk right on in and harmony them. This will get all newbies in your group all excited as they see you pull mobs one by one.
When I was your level I could do this camp together with a good tank - damn the exp was good :wink: There is also a undead spawn near there so if you're out of dervs and group has alot of mana and health you can pull from there to get some Mummies and Ghouls!

Derv 3 is almost at the zone to Oasis.. at the West Wall (SW corner of the zone).
There are 3 spawns here and you can solo it with a tank or well, whatever actually. If you're with a caster you can harmony them, snare one, and then nuke it down. Should be easy. Then do that again until the mob is dead.

I got 5 yellow bubs with my newbie cleric yesterday at derv 2. We didn't have a druid but the cleric soothe worked like a charm :)
We had a VERY good time, pulling both scarabs and ghouls, mummies and dervs! The group ranged from 10 to 14 (I went from 11 to 12 woot!). I think it took about 3 hours to get 5 yellow bubs from 11 1/2 to 12 1/2 and damn the groupchannel went HOT during that time hehe. I can tell ya that I haven't had that much fun in a while :)

Good luck, this is just one of many places :)
[/quote]</TEXTAREA>
